    {
      "key": "fc989d06-56e1-4686-82d3-96b99d0ca0e5",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "- **This is a pilot, so things change!** Please always refer to the Slide Decks and Speaker Notes for the latest updates.\n- If the rest of this lesson plan is blank, don't worry! It just means we're still in the process of updating this lesson plan on our website and that process can sometimes get delayed! However, **the slides are always up to date** and the speaker notes contain everything you need to run the lesson. "
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fc989d06-56e1-4686-82d3-96b99d0ca0e5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "22dcc871-b271-4c8f-901b-6f9bb0e6e8f2"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ee59639d-a169-4af0-9b0d-3a8c6ae73d74",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:**  Watch the [Spotlight: Henny Tha Bizness](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OrrZPzgWPII) video\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** What is one example from the video of how Henny combines music and technology?\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should identify how Henny uses an editing machine to combine the tracks for songs, similar to how students use music lab. They may also notice how Henny applies effects to track using this technology.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> A record producer is just one example of someone who combines music and technology similar to what we've been doing in music lab. Today, we're going to apply what we've been learning similar to how a record producer works with tracks and artists."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ee59639d-a169-4af0-9b0d-3a8c6ae73d74",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b5ef3ffa-f4c9-453d-895d-5707e622d93e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d6827ff1-6012-4ca6-8e5b-9c978264ee7c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> We're going to start with a quick review of some skills from this week and a check-in level. Once you've passed the check-in, we'll continue to learn more about Henny and how he uses effects.\n\n",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "**Opportunity for Differentiation:** These first few levels are designed to provide an opportunity for differentiation or individual intervention. Students who may have been absent or struggling so far can spend additional time in these levels (or revisiting previous assessments) before continuing to the rest of the lesson. Otherwise, students can complete the quick check-in to reinforce the skills from this unit and then continue to the career spotlight."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d6827ff1-6012-4ca6-8e5b-9c978264ee7c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c7477057-dbfb-4037-8a76-4e9658283e40"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d0de8363-1dbc-473d-9e7a-c24ee37b4690",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students log into the Skill Review level. These levels are a review of all of the skills students have seen in the last two lessons. \n- If students feel confident in what they've been learning, have them continue to the Check-In level.\n- If students have been absent or need a review, have them review the sublevels before continuing to the Check-In",
        "progression_name": "Skill Review"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d0de8363-1dbc-473d-9e7a-c24ee37b4690",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c7477057-dbfb-4037-8a76-4e9658283e40"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "614c6a0d-f3b3-41b7-a4e8-c9cf13c0a794",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Check-In",
        "progression_name": "Check-in",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "**Formative Assessment**: This level is the last assessment before the mini-project in the next lesson - consider checking the level during class and providing targeted intervention if students are struggling. Ideally any lingering issues can be addressed here before continuing to the more open-ended project and the rest of the unit."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "614c6a0d-f3b3-41b7-a4e8-c9cf13c0a794",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c7477057-dbfb-4037-8a76-4e9658283e40"
      }
    },
