    {
      "key": "724a0a77-c5a0-41a5-a35f-603158f63031",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "After reviewing the project guide and rubric, you can view an exemplar for this project in our self-paced professional learning course. [**Click here to view the exemplar**](https://studio.code.org/s/self-paced-pl-teaching-computer-science-discoveries-music-lab/lessons/2/levels/20)",
        "name": "Project Exemplar"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "724a0a77-c5a0-41a5-a35f-603158f63031",
        "lesson_activity.key": "976d781f-a07d-4321-b589-e7389e242a99"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "76c6f196-6c9c-4f9c-bdfb-757ace4e5810",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Who is a character in a movie or show who has a distinctive musical theme? Where every time you hear the music, you think of that character?\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** It may take some time for students to think of examples here, but once they hear a few they may be more likely to come up with additional examples. Another way to frame this question is: if you were walking by a room and heard this musical theme, you'd know what movie or show someone was watching Some examples you could supply are:\n- [Bluey](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8nv1m-aTCZI) has a very distinctive theme song\n- [Harry Potter](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wtHra9tFISY) has a distinctive theme\n- Baseball players or wrestlers have distinctive music for when they enter an arena\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> Today we're going to apply everything we've learned so far to create Walk-Up songs for different characters in books or TV shows! In order to make these songs, we're going to learn about a new feature in music lab: Triggers!"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "76c6f196-6c9c-4f9c-bdfb-757ace4e5810",
        "lesson_activity.key": "516f6711-0881-4888-b5d8-7ef260dd7e40"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7ebb4d49-3ce2-4011-b4d3-4869b540cdcf",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Pass out a copy of the [Walk Up Songs Activity Guide](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-NOQXuyOA4TXy2X4oACt97K0f64h2TlkP2tc3-YQKRI/edit) to each student\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the Overview as a class\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Define portion of the activity guide\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students login to Music Lab to complete the Trigger levels and the Prepare portion of the activity guide",
        "progression_name": "Triggers"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7ebb4d49-3ce2-4011-b4d3-4869b540cdcf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d9f8da8-6f8c-43cf-8a9b-55292a187d92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ff0b9b76-4cb2-4689-9ff0-ce04439c3c59",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Prepare"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ff0b9b76-4cb2-4689-9ff0-ce04439c3c59",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d9f8da8-6f8c-43cf-8a9b-55292a187d92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "185e350d-e4ba-4689-9e0f-e2b78df65ded",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Check in with students as they complete the Trigger levels and the Prepare steps. They should check in with you before continuing to try and code their walk-up songs.\n\nOnce you've approved students progress so far, hand out a copy of the [Walk Up Songs Rubric](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1poW9kQYsXnBX2w7jCKhN9qjTbJ52qRDrn8jZf62S3-g/edit?tab=t.0) for students to use while coding. Then they can continue to the next levels."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "185e350d-e4ba-4689-9e0f-e2b78df65ded",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d9f8da8-6f8c-43cf-8a9b-55292a187d92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "113bb6b0-5147-4d87-8bcd-0fd4f4cb73d1",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Walk-Up Songs"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "113bb6b0-5147-4d87-8bcd-0fd4f4cb73d1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d9f8da8-6f8c-43cf-8a9b-55292a187d92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7e54404f-6dd8-4f1a-bc92-f8a316f07b08",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **(Optional) Do This:** Students who finish their walk-up songs can participate in this Partner Game:\n- Tell your partners who your three characters are and describe the character's personalities.\n- Play one of your Walk-Up songs without saying which character it belongs to.\n- Allow your partner to match the song to a character.\n- Ask them to explain their choice.\n- If they guess wrong, listen to their explanation and adjust your code to make the song fit the character better.\n- Repeat with new partners until someone guesses all three correctly!",
        "progression_name": "(Optional) Partner Game"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7e54404f-6dd8-4f1a-bc92-f8a316f07b08",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d9f8da8-6f8c-43cf-8a9b-55292a187d92"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "89354d45-239a-4fbd-9fc8-74e85ef8b94a",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "89354d45-239a-4fbd-9fc8-74e85ef8b94a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7d9f8da8-6f8c-43cf-8a9b-55292a187d92"
      }
    },
