    {
      "key": "53e5182b-ad4d-4c53-99dc-af7747e0659e",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "After reviewing the project guide and rubric, you can view an exemplar for this project in our self-paced professional learning course. [**Click here to view the exemplar**](https://studio.code.org/s/self-paced-pl-teaching-computer-science-discoveries-music-lab/lessons/3/levels/19)",
        "name": "Project Exemplar"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "53e5182b-ad4d-4c53-99dc-af7747e0659e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d04fb5be-ab67-4ab9-930f-d9e9e701f2d0"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b6fa22e8-e5f4-4ee8-a081-552811ef9342",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** What's an example of something visual that you've seen loop forever? What are those visuals usually trying to communicate?\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** It may take some time for students to think of examples here, but once they hear a few they may be more likely to come up with additional examples. Once clear example are gifs or memes, which usually try to communicate something silly or funny but can also provide satire or social commentary. Students may also think of public safety animations, such as a crossing-guard animation saying it is okay to cross or you need to stop. These types of visuals communicate safety information. When it seems like students have surfaced several examples, continue with the discussion\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the slide with several cat GIFs on it\n\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-microphone\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> <strong>Say:</strong> Today we're going to combine visual loops and sound loops by adding a looped backing track to a cat GIF of your choice. You will need to determine the mood or vibe of your particular gif and create a song that matches this mood. To make things more interesting, we're also going to learn how we can randomize tracks in a song to add to make our song more unexpected."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b6fa22e8-e5f4-4ee8-a081-552811ef9342",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ffe5579a-d1da-44db-97ec-1b80761ff425"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "963171d2-09c2-485a-9374-29dc7cfd8753",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Pass out a copy of the [Cat GIFs Activity Guide](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JQWXQ39-DKoE2gbwLi7v-BdV0Dcn3Z9IMY0515-pKVI/edit) to each student\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the Overview as a class\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the Define portion of the activity guide\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students login to Music Lab to complete the Play Random levels and the Prepare portion of the activity guide",
        "progression_name": "Play Random"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "963171d2-09c2-485a-9374-29dc7cfd8753",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f95b14e2-6381-4410-a951-1f33764e6ec9"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6f019149-f344-414c-aa2e-2fd930a6c6b7",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Prepare"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6f019149-f344-414c-aa2e-2fd930a6c6b7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f95b14e2-6381-4410-a951-1f33764e6ec9"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2671e45f-3a29-49b0-a0dd-42f66fd70a68",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Check in with students as they complete the Trigger levels and the Prepare steps. They should check in with you before continuing to try and code their walk-up songs.\n\nOnce you've approved students progress so far, hand out a copy of the [Cat GIF Loops Rubric](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ZW8gD3eA3lXAur9_PSC8nL2h6VJrcW2fBC3rxwm8Moc/edit?tab=t.0). Then they can continue to the next levels.",
        "progression_name": "Musical Cat GIFs"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2671e45f-3a29-49b0-a0dd-42f66fd70a68",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f95b14e2-6381-4410-a951-1f33764e6ec9"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0b370749-a2aa-41e1-ad35-eb2de61b15c8",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Share Out:** Have students share their work with their peers in some way. Their peers can provide feedback using \"I like...\" and \"What if...\" sentence stems to provide positive constructive feedback. Some options could be:\n- **Class Shareout:** Ask for volunteers and let them share their songs with the whole class, then choose 2-3 students to provide feedback\n- **Pair Networking:** Have students pair up and share their songs and provide feedback, then swap to a new pair\n- **Gallery Walk:** Have students leave their song open on their computer, then walk around and visit other songs. Students carry post-it notes with them and leave feedback on any students they visit."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0b370749-a2aa-41e1-ad35-eb2de61b15c8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "cb7f4200-865f-4ea3-b387-2c5dcc82d731"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "43cb3bf3-4ce3-4bf3-a0f7-493b93c31700",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Have students complete the survey on the last level of the lesson. ",
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "43cb3bf3-4ce3-4bf3-a0f7-493b93c31700",
